---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageIntro from "../components/PageIntro.astro";
import RelatedLinks from "../components/RelatedLinks.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FAQ | Kamatamare Sanuki English Guide"
  description="Find clear answers about tickets, seating, language, photos, weather, family visits, and attending your first Kamatamare Sanuki match in Kagawa."
>
  <PageIntro
    eyebrow="Your first match, made easier"
    title="Frequently Asked Questions"
    description="Simple answers to help you feel prepared and enjoy the day."
  />
  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container container--narrow prose intro-copy">
      <h2>It is okay to be new</h2>
      <p>
        You do not need to know Japanese football or understand every stadium custom. Arrive with
        enough time, follow staff directions, and ask for help when you need it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Match-specific arrangements can change. Use these answers as a starting point, then check
        the official club information before travelling.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="container container--narrow faq-list">
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Can I go to a match alone?</h2>
        <p>
          Yes. Many people attend football matches alone. Choose a seat where you feel
          comfortable, arrive early, and ask stadium staff if you are unsure where to go.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Do I need to speak Japanese?</h2>
        <p>
          No. Most information may be in Japanese, but you can manage with simple English,
          gestures, and your ticket screen. Keeping the stadium name and return route on your
          phone can also help.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Where can I check the official schedule?</h2>
        <p>
          Use the
          <a href="https://www.kamatamare.jp/match/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
            >official match schedule</a
          >. Confirm the date, kick-off time, home or away status, and venue shortly before your
          visit.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Can I buy tickets on matchday?</h2>
        <p>
          Yes. Matchday tickets are normally available, so you can still attend if you have not
          bought one in advance. However, sales methods and available seats can change, and some
          matches or seat types may sell out. Check the
          <a href="https://www.kamatamare.jp/ticket/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
            >official ticket page</a
          > before you travel.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Which seat is best for first-time visitors?</h2>
        <p>
          A main-stand seat is often a comfortable choice because it gives a clear view of the
          whole pitch. The main stand has a roof, which provides shade from the strong summer sun
          and shelter from rain. A reserved seat can also make arrival easier.
        </p>
        <p>
          The back stand does not have a roof, so prepare for direct sun or rain if you sit there.
          Seat names and supporter rules may change, so read the official ticket description
          before buying.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Can I take photos?</h2>
        <p>
          Personal photos are generally fine if you do not block another person's view or disturb
          the match. Commercial use and some video sharing are restricted. Check the
          <a href="https://www.kamatamare.jp/match/manner.php" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
            >official matchday rules</a
          > before posting photos or video online.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>What should I bring?</h2>
        <p>
          Bring your ticket or QR code, a charged phone, a payment card, some cash, and clothing
          for the weather. Water, sun protection, or an extra layer may be useful. Check current
          bag and container rules before leaving.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>What happens if it rains?</h2>
        <p>
          Matches usually continue in rain unless conditions are unsafe. Some seats may have
          limited cover. Bring a compact raincoat rather than relying on an umbrella in the
          seating area, and check official announcements for any cancellation or delay.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Is the stadium family-friendly?</h2>
        <p>
          Families are welcome. Arrive early so children have time to become familiar with the
          stadium, toilets, and seating area. Ticket rules for children and matchday activities
          can vary, so confirm them on the official match page.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Is this an official guide?</h2>
        <p>
          No. This is an independent personal fan-made guide. It is not operated or approved by
          Kamatamare Sanuki or the J.League. Official information always takes priority.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <div class="official-box">
        <h2>Check once more before you go</h2>
        <p>
          The schedule, tickets, transport, entry times, and stadium rules may change for each
          match.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a
            class="text-link"
            href="https://www.kamatamare.jp/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer">Visit the official Kamatamare Sanuki website</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <RelatedLinks
    links={[
      {
        label: "Stadium & Access",
        href: "/stadium/",
        description: "Plan your route and review a simple matchday checklist.",
      },
      {
        label: "About this guide",
        href: "/about/",
        description: "Read the scope and limitations of this independent guide.",
      },
      {
        label: "Club History",
        href: "/history/",
        description: "Meet the club before you arrive at the stadium.",
      },
    ]}
  />
</BaseLayout>
